CatDescriptText: Cutline of related image published in Pittsburgh Courier newspaper, November 12, 1966, pg. 4B reads: "The Rangerettes -Elk dignitaries from many places were on hand to help the Rangerettes of Western Pennsylvania celebrate their 15th anniversary recently.  Seated: Elizabeth Madden, honoree; Hester R. Thomas, State President; Nettie B. Smith, Grand Daughter Ruler of New York City; Clara Randolph, Deputy, and Alice Wilkerson, Captain.  Standing: Past Captain, Edmonia Harrington, Bessie Woods, Beatrice Dickey, James Madden, husband of honoree; Dorothy Lowery, Past Captain; Claire Smith, co-chairman; Alice Crisp, William Long, Davis Kirk, Georgia Robinson, Sarah Norton, Florence Johnson and Mabel Meek. - Harris Photo."
TitMainTitle: Group portrait of Elks and Rangerettes members, most wearing light colored sleeveless jacquard dresses, and gloves, gathered in North Side Elks lodge for Rangerettes fifteenth anniversary party, another version
